<br>
Okay, I finally got around to trying this out.  This info might be useful to any other <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  evil <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  mages out there, so here's how it went...<br>
<br>
I zoned into Sol A and immediately summoned an earth pet (I'm level 49 by the way).  I slowly made my way towards the gnome castle, and yes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> everything</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in this entire dungeon will and does agro on me when I get within agro range.  At ALL times on the way down, the pet had BO2 and Sheild of Lava on.  Things were a breeze until getting to the 2 gnome conjurers just before the castle, but they went down and I had 2 bubs health left.  I did not blast anything the whole time.. only healed pet.<br>
<br>
Once I healed up some, I told pet to stay guard in hallway and I peeked around the corner and pulled a guard using Cancel Magic.  Of course, both came.. but they came without agroing the rest of the castle.<br>
<br>
Guards went down easily; next was the wandering gnome inside the front gate.  I slowly approached in attempt to pull only him, but he came with friends.. including Gabbie and her posse.  The pet came running into the hallway and went to work.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> THIS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is the important part when breaking in the room... do not attempt blasting the mobs down, just stand far back and heal the pet.  I stood out in front of the castle and healed my pet continuously the entire time.  No mobs attacked me... they were ALL on the pet and stayed there.  I used an entire mana bar just keeping the pet up, but I was never touched.  We all know that we, as mages, are useless without our pet.  Of course it may work to blast the mobs too, but I personally would rather be untouched with a pet than be oom with a dead/dying pet, and this worked. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One more word of advice..<br>
Once in the room, it's a breeze.  The pet can easily handle this room alone.  This is the part where I stand there staring at walls wishing I could hang out invis'ed with pet still intact.  I decided to stand against the wall opposite of Gabbie's spot between the 2 stacks of boxes so the spawns would hit my pet rather than me.  This was a bad decision.. a few minutes later, I was attacked through the wall, Jobaber took off out the door, the room filled with gnome-bots, and I gated with less than 100 HP's left... with no cloak and no time left to rebreak in because of this thing that sometimes interferes with my game time... work.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Point here is... no matter what people tell you... if you are evil or kos to these gnomes, going in here solo isn't as easy as some say.  You can't pull one at a time. <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kimmi_sc/teldiva_grimleux.jpg>
